cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper discusses hardware designs for spiking neural networks and their potential applications, which falls under the category of neural networks and artificial intelligence (cs.NE). It also touches on energy efficiency, which is relevant to embedded systems (cs.ET) and architecture (cs.AR). The comparison between spiking and non-spiking systems involves computational efficiency, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
